definition: to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]
to sign one's name/visa/variant of 籤|签[qian1]
certificate/proof/to prove/to demonstrate/to confirm/variant of 症[zheng4]

sentences.english: We are up to our knees with applications for entry visa.
sentences.chinese: 我們收到很多很多要求入境簽證的申請書。

sentences.english: Bill Berger leads the U.S. Disaster Assistance Response Team, whose members are waiting for visas in Bangkok.
sentences.chinese: 美國救災應急小組的成員正在曼谷等待入境簽證。

sentences.english: Is there anything wrong with my passport or the entry visa?
sentences.chinese: 我的護照或者入境簽證出了什麼問題嗎？

sentences.english: She is granted a non - resident visa .
sentences.chinese: 她拿到了非定居入境簽證。

sentences.english: The Controller of immigration has approved a Single-Journey Entry Visa for this foreigner.
sentences.chinese: 入境管理局已經認可了該名外國人的單程入境簽證。

sentences.english: I only have a single-entry visa.
sentences.chinese: 我的是一次性入境簽證。

sentences.english: We'll complete the formalities for your entry visa as soon as possible.
sentences.chinese: 我們會盡快辦妥您的入境簽證手續的。
